{
  "texts": [
    "Reported sample units varied quite widely across papers with many reporting only the number of documents used.",
    "Document types were similarly variable and specific to research contexts.",
    "For example, several papers reported training sample sizes as the number of clinical notes, number of published abstracts, or number of scraped tweets.",
    "In contrast, some papers reported sample size using non-context-specific measures such as sentences, entities, or tokens.",
    "Given this variety, we classified sample units as belonging to 1 of 6 common categories: clinical notes or reports, sentences, abstracts or papers, entities, tokens, or others."
  ]
}